file.name: nytimes.com-times_tags-1.0.0-swagger.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  description: With the TimesTags API, you can mine the riches of the New York Times tag
    set. The TimesTags service matches your query to the controlled vocabularies
    that fuel NYTimes.com metadata. You supply a string of characters, and the
    service returns a ranked list of suggested terms.
  termsOfService: http://developer.nytimes.com/tou
  title: TimesTags
  version: 1.0.0
  x-apiClientRegistration:
    url: http://developer.nytimes.com/signup
  x-apisguru-categories:
    - media
    - open_data
  x-logo:
    url: https://static01.nyt.com/images/icons/t_logo_291_black.png
  x-origin:
    - format: swagger
      url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/NYTimes/public_api_specs/master/times_tags/times_tags_v3.json
      version: "2.0"
  x-providerName: nytimes.com
  x-serviceName: times_tags
externalDocs:
  url: http://developer.nytimes.com/
security:
  - apikey: []
paths:
  /timestags:
    get:
      parameters:
        - description: Your search query
          in: query
          name: query
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: >
            If you do not specify a value for filter (see the Optional
            Parameters), your query will be matched to tags in all four Times
            dictionaries: subject, geographic location, organization and person.
            To use more than one, separate with commas.
          in: query
          name: filter
          required: false
          schema:
            type: string
            enum:
              - Des
              - Geo
              - Org
              - Per
        - description: Sets the maximum number of results
          in: query
          name: max
          required: false
          schema:
            type: integer
            default: 10
      responses:
        "200":
          description: An array of tags
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                items:
                  items:
                    type: string
                  type: array
                type: array
servers:
  - url: http://api.nytimes.com/svc/suggest/v1
  - url: https://api.nytimes.com/svc/suggest/v1
components:
  securitySchemes:
    apikey:
      in: query
      name: api-key
      type: apiKey
